---
title: Forms
---

{% block head %}
<script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.7.1.min.js" integrity="sha256-/JqT3SQfawRcv/BIHPThkBvs0OEvtFFmqPF/lYI/Cxo=" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>

{% include "partials/global/form-validator.njk" %} {% endblock %}

<header class="page-header">
  <h1>{{ title }}</h1>
</header>

<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-8">
    <form id="registration" novalidate>
      <div
        tabindex="-1"
        role="group"
        id="errorSummary"
        class="alert alert-danger errorSummary d-none"
      ></div>

      <fieldset>
        <legend>Your details</legend>
          <div class="help-block">
              Here is some instructional text about completing this input successfully.
          </div>
        <div class="row">
          <div class="form-group field col-6">
            <label class="form-label" for="name">Name</label>
            <input
              class="form-control mb-2"
              type="text"
              name="name"
              id="name"
              autocomplete="given-name"
            />
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="row">
                <div class="form-group field col-6">
                  <label class="form-label" for="email">
                    <span class="field-label"
                      >Email <span class="field-required">(Required)</span></span
                    >
                    <span class="field-hint">A valid email address</span>
                  </label>
                  <input
                    class="form-control mb-2"
                    type="email"
                    name="email"
                    id="email"
                    autocomplete="email"
                    aria-required="true"
                  />
                </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">

        <div class="form-group field col-6">
          <label class="form-label" for="password">
            <span class="field-label">Password <span class="field-required">(Required)</span></span>
            <span class="field-hint">Longer than 8 characters</span>
          </label>
          <input
            class="form-control"
            type="password"
            name="password"
            id="password"
            autocomplete="current-password"
            aria-required="true"
            min-length="8"
          />
        </div>
        </div>

      <div class="row">
        <div class="form-group field">
          <label class="form-label" for="otp">
            <span class="field-label">One-time code <span class="field-required">(Required)</span></span>
          </label>
          <div class="col-2">
          <input
            class="form-control"
            type="otp"
            name="otp"
            id="otp"
            autocomplete="one-time-password"
            aria-required="true"
            min-length="6"
            max-length="6"
          />
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    </fieldset>

    <fieldset>
      <legend>Date ranges</legend>

      <div class="row">

        <div class="col-auto">
        <p class="help-block my-2">
          I am a help block. Here is some instructional text about completing this input successfully.
        </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row">
        <div class="col-sm-3">
          <div class="form-group field">
            <label class="form-label" for="date--start">
              <span class="field-label">Start date <span class="field-required">(Required)</span></span>
            </label>

            <div class="input-group">
              <input id="date--start" required type="text" class="form-control" placeholder="YYYY-MM-DD" aria-label="Recipient's username" aria-describedby="button-addon-start">
              <button class="btn btn-outline-primary" type="button" id="button-addon-start">
                <div class="visually-hidden">Open date picker</div>
                <i class="far fa-calendar-alt"></i></button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-sm-3">
          <div class="form-group field">

            <label class="form-label" for="date--end">
              <span class="field-label">End date <span class="field-required">(Required)</span></span>
            </label>

            <div class="input-group">
              <input id="date--end" type="text" required class="form-control" placeholder="YYYY-MM-DD" aria-describedby="button-addon-end">
              <button class="btn btn-outline-primary" type="button" id="button-addon-end">
                <div class="visually-hidden">Open date picker</div>
                <i class="far fa-calendar-alt"></i></button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </fieldset>

    <div class="row">
      <div class="form-group field col-6">
        <label class="form-label" for="custom-select-again">
          <span class="field-label">Options</span>
        </label>
        <select class="form-select" id="custom-select-again">
          <option>1 (One)</option>
          <option>2 (Two)</option>
          <option>3 (Three)</option>
          <option>4 (Four)</option>
          <option>5 (Five)</option>
        </select>
      </div>
</div>

      <div class="form-group field">
        <label class="form-label" for="message">
          <span class="field-label">Comment</span>
          <span class="field-hint"
            >Tell us a little about yourself, in 240 characters or less.</span
          >
        </label>
        <textarea
          class="form-control"
          type="message"
          name="message"
          id="message"
          aria-required="true"
        ></textarea>
      </div>

      <fieldset>
        <legend>Pick a side</legend>
        <div class="form-check">
          <input
            class="form-check-input"
            type="radio"
            id="radio"
            name="radio"
          />
          <label class="form-check-label form-label" for="radio">Left</label>
        </div>

        <div class="form-check">
          <input
            class="form-check-input"
            type="radio"
            id="radio-checked"
            name="radio"
          />
          <label class="form-check-label form-label" for="radio-checked"
            >Right</label
          >
        </div>

        <div class="form-check">
          <input
            class="form-check-input"
            type="radio"
            id="radio-checked-again"
            name="radio"
          />
          <label class="form-check-label form-label" for="radio-checked-again"
            >Sit on the fence</label
          >
        </div>
      </fieldset>

      <div class="form-check">
        <input
          class="form-check-input"
          type="checkbox"
          id="check"
          name="check"
        />
        <label class="form-check-label form-label" for="check"
          >Opt-in to our amazing newsletter</label
        >
      </div>

<div class="row">
      <div class="form-group col-6">
        <label class="form-label" for="exampleInputFile-jazzy">
          <span class="field-label">File input</span>
          <span class="field-hint">Pick a file… any file…</span>
        </label>
        <input class="form-control" type="file" id="exampleInputFile-jazzy" />
      </div>
</div>
      <div class="controls mb-5">
        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Login</button>
        <button type="reset" class="btn btn-default">Clear</button>
      </div>
    </form>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-4">
    <h2>Guidelines</h2>
    <ol>
      <li><code>novalidate</code> set on form to disable browser validation</li>
      <li>Top-aligned labels</li>
      <li>Labels always visible</li>
      <li>A new row for each question</li>
      <li>
          Only use the character count component when there is a good reason for limiting the number of characters users can enter.
          When using this component:
        <ul>
          <li>
            Display how many characters the user has remaining as they type.
          </li>
          <li>
            Display the remaining characters below the text area.
          </li>
          <li>
            Allow the user to enter more characters than the maximum limit. The form validation will handle any excess.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        Use the appropriate <code>autocomplete</code> attribute for the field in
        question.
        <a
          href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Attributes/autocomplete"
          >View the list of values at MDN</a
        >
      </li>
      <li>
        All fields optional by default; explicitly mark those which are
        required.
      </li>
      <li>
        Use a <code>fieldset</code> to group multiple controls. A
        <code>legend</code> describes a group like a
        <code>label</code> describes an individual control.
      </li>
      <li>Use sensible defaults: design for common circumstances first.</li>
      <li>
        The input width gives users a clue as to the length of the content it
        requires.
      </li>
      <li>
        Do not disable the form submit button: allow it to be discovered and
        trigger the form validation rules.
      </li>
    </ol>

    <h3>Validation</h3>
    <p>Messsages should:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Be concise</li>
      <li>Be consistent</li>
      <li>Be specific</li>
      <li>Avoid jargon</li>
      <li>Use plain language</li>
      <li>Use active voice</li>
      <li>Not blame the user</li>
    </ol>
  </div>
</div>
